- \cf3 Beaudry Galizia Portier 2018 Restud: \cf0 Link Hayek\'92s view to Keynes\'92 one. Hayek maintains that recessions reflect period of needed liquidations resulting from past over-investment. Keynes views recession as periods of deficient demand that should be counteracted with policy intervention. This paper reconciles both view by asserting modelling the trade-off and concluding that while policy intervention postpones the adjustment, some of it is still needed during recessions. \
