- \cf3 Benhabib Wang 2013 JME: \cf0 model with financial constraint that generates indeterminacy of equilibria. In this context, shocks of all kinds produce boom-bust dynamics. Labor demand is effectively upward sloping and steeper than labor supply, this is due to the presence of an incentive compatibility constraint which gives pro cyclical lending, if one HH lends then also others are incentivized to do so, hence strategic complementarity in actions. \
\
- \cf3 Benhabib Wen 2003 JME: \cf0 RBC model with externality - generates indeterminacy and boom and bust responses \
\
- \cf3  Benhabib Dong Wang: \cf0 otherwise standard RBC model with adverse selection. It generates two steady states (as shown in Wilson 1980) and indeterminacy due to (de facto) increasing returns generated by the pro cyclical variations in the fraction of honest borrowers resulting in a countercyclical markup (as in Benhabib and Farmer 1994) \
